title: Test
summary: This grouped bar chart has 6 categories of State on the x axis representing 2 groups: Dispensary price, and Street price.
Averaging these 2 groups, the highest category is found for State Michigan with a mean value of 287.5.
Followed by Arizona with a mean value of 272.0.
The lowest category is observed at Oregon that has a mean value of 202.5
showing a difference of 34.7% with the maximum value.
In case of Michigan, Dispensary price shows more dominance than any other State with a value 301.0 and it has the lowest value 214.0 in Oregon.
